CC0 1.0 Universal

Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer
exclusive copyright and related rights ("Copyright") upon the creator and
subsequent owner(s) ("Copyright Holder") of an original work of authorship
and/or a database (each, a "Work").  The Copyright Holder may, in certain
circumstances, voluntarily relinquish those Copyrights and related rights in
the Work and publicly place the Work into the public domain.

CC0 is a public domain dedication tool.  When applying CC0 to a Work, the
Copyright Holder relinquishes, to the fullest extent allowed by law, all of
their copyright and related rights in the Work worldwide, under copyright law
and all related legal or equitable rights, such as publicity and database
rights.

The full legal text is available at:
https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode

----- END LICENSE TEXT -----
